@

The verifier walks the captured MP135 UART stream
(`streams/mp135.uart.bin`) for the bench summary line that the
firmware prints once the streaming read has been validated against
the incrementing pattern. The line carries `<mode> @ presc=<N>`
plus elapsed time, effective Mbps, and a `firsterr=<offset>` field
that is `-1` only when every byte of the megabyte matched. A bullet
check passes iff the matching bench line exists and reports
`firsterr=-1`. The verifier prints the configured SCLK, firmware
effective Mbps, test-server wall time between the `bench_start`
and `bench_done` marks, and a wall-rate computed from requested payload
bits divided by measured wall time next to each prescaler result. There
is no JEDEC or flash-protocol surface to assert here --- the slave just
streams raw bytes, so the firsterr sentinel is the entire correctness
contract.

